eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 10 Years
Maximum age: 60 Years
This trial does not accept healthy volunteers.

Monoclonal gammopathy of undetermined significance (MGUS), smoldering myeloma, or
             Waldenstrom's macroglobulinemia

Patients must have relapsed or refractory CD20-positive diffuse large B-cell lymphoma (includes morphological variants: centroblastic, immunoblastic, T-cell/histiocyte-rich, and anaplastic, CD20-positive mediastinal [thymic] and intravascular large B-cell lymphoma subtypes)

groups.description: Veliparib on Day -2 through 5 of a 21-day cycle. In addition, carboplatin and paclitaxel will be administered on Day 1 of a 21-day cycle.
groups.name: Veliparib with Carboplatin and Paclitaxel

groups.description: Patients with completely resectable stage I-IV RCC undergo surgical resection. Patients with incompletely resectable stage III-IV RCC undergo treatment as per physician's choice.
groups.name: Surgery

outcome_measures.analysis_method: The proportion of disagreements across all time points will be estimated with an intercept-only GEE regression model that accounts for correlation among measures from the same patient. This proportion will be reported with a 95% confidence interval.
outcome_measures.measure: Frequency with which CT and qualitative FDG-PET disagree in their classifications of response

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Days from randomization to the second objective radiographic progression or death of any cause after the first objective radiographic progression, whichever occurs first
outcome_measures.time_frame: Measured up to 5 years after the last subject has enrolled in the study.

outcome_measures.measure: In patients with the JAK2V617F mutation, change in peripheral blood granulocyte JAK2V617F allele burden from baseline to Cycle 3 EOC, to Cycle 6 EOC and at the end of every third cycle thereafter until Cycle 12 EOC and EOT
Percentage of eligible patients able to receive an allogeneic stem cell transplantation
